Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET) was followed by a primetime presentation (8-11 p.m. ET/PT).\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beginning with Friday's Opening Ceremony, NBCUniversal has a posted three-day Total Audience Delivery average of 34.5 million viewers across the combined live Paris Prime (2-5 p.m.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9977816315547892, \"rank\": 0.0020384636831085653, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9995572929598807, \"rank\": 0.0004429007055980406, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1482, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996607585, \"rank\": 3.394229735323324e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET) and U.S. primetime (8-11 p.m. ET/PT) time periods - up 79% from Tokyo (19.3 million).\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999980465873, \"rank\": 1.943231400762346e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A pair of U.S. victories in team sports also delivered audience milestones on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. men's basketball team averaged 10.9 million viewers on NBC and Peacock - alarger audience than for its victory in the Tokyo Olympics gold-medal game(9.3 million) - in winning its opener against Serbia.\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1687, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999797969893663, \"rank\": 1.9332898076370636e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.8290821649666731, \"rank\": 0.19602280763439842, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.6448924670964833, \"rank\": 0.5506413287782153, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later in the day, the U.S. women's soccer team's win over Germany topped all men's and women's matches in the Tokyo and Rio Olympics, with an average of 4.2 million viewers on USA Network and Peacock.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.6798511142515113, \"rank\": 0.2599309324034082, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2004, \"end\": 2009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999980465873, \"rank\": 1.943231400762346e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2014, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5451302382671092e-22, \"text\": \"Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.9999417165959753, \"rank\": 5.828680101157714e-05, \"text\": \"USA Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}, {\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999996398401, \"rank\": 3.594418702247844e-10, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peacock Powers Streaming Milestones    Led by Peacock, 4.5 billion minutes of Paris Olympics coverage has been streamed through Sunday -surpassing the entire Tokyo Olympics(4.48 billion minutes across NBCUniversal digital platforms).\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2331, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9995572929598807, \"rank\": 0.0004429007055980406, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympics Opening Weekend grew on Peacock as Sunday, July 28 surpassed Saturday, July 27 as itssecond-best day of engagement ever, behind only thePeacock AFC Wild Card Exclusive, which was the most live-streamed event in U.S. history.\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2335, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2374, \"end\": 2381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999996398401, \"rank\": 3.594418702247844e-10, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 2561, \"end\": 2565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999797969893663, \"rank\": 1.9332898076370636e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sunday's coverage was streamed by 6.0 million viewers on Peacock and NBCU Digital platforms.\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999996398401, \"rank\": 3.594418702247844e-10, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 2647, \"end\": 2651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympics Delivers for Brands    Only three days in, advertisements in the Paris Olympics on NBCUniversal are already delivering impact for brands throughout the funnel - at incredible scale.\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2772, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9995572929598807, \"rank\": 0.0004429007055980406, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, advertisers are seeing higher attention on their ads (+18%), greater message recall (+33%) and an increased likelihood to search (+67%) on linear than competitive broadcast/cable television.\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 3070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These Olympics are reaching key target audiences and delivering unparalleled impact for advertisers across key categories, including:  Sources: iSpot attention index, NBC (7/26-28); Marketcast TVBE, P18-49, NBC Prime vs. competitive broadcast/cable TV (7/26-27); EDO SER vs. auto category in competitive broadcast/cable TV (7/26-28); NBCU in-house audience insights utilizing 1P/3P data (7/26)  Total Audience Delivery is based upon live-plus-same day custom fast national figures from Nielsen and digital data from Adobe Analytics.\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3241, \"end\": 3244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.8290821649666731, \"rank\": 0.19602280763439842, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re